00:01:03.210 --> 00:01:04.890
That's why how come we're here.

00:01:04.890 --> 00:01:06.990
TOM: As the older
generation, who

00:01:06.990 --> 00:01:11.090
hasn't grown up with apps, the
jargon and the lingo you hear

00:01:11.090 --> 00:01:12.690
is very intimidating.

00:01:12.690 --> 00:01:17.780
But when you actually start to
get into it, it's very simple.

00:01:17.780 --> 00:01:18.800
It's very logical.

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:21.130
And once you learn
the steps, they

00:01:21.130 --> 00:01:23.300
follow one after the other.

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:26.090
And so it's almost
like a cookbook recipe.

00:01:26.090 --> 00:01:28.420
If you can cook something
out of a cookbook,

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:29.680
you could write an app.

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:34.120
MALE SPEAKER: Today we wanted
