FEMALE SPEAKER: OK.

00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:45.370
DAN GALPIN: Hi, I'm Dan Galpin.

00:02:45.370 --> 00:02:47.036
I'm a developer
advocate here at Google.

00:02:47.036 --> 00:02:49.800
I help to build both Android
fundamentals and the advanced

00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:51.180
Android class.

00:02:51.180 --> 00:02:52.250
This was a great day.

00:02:52.250 --> 00:02:54.070
We had an incredible
number of people,

00:02:54.070 --> 00:02:56.320
and everyone pretty much
got through the content.

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:57.360
And that was the
exciting for me,

00:02:57.360 --> 00:02:59.901
was watching people's eyes light
up, who had never programmed

00:02:59.901 --> 00:03:02.390
before, who were now starting
to think of themselves

00:03:02.390 --> 00:03:04.760
as being programmers
for the first time.

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:06.800
And everybody danced at the end.

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:08.316
That was really the key thing.

